@Adam 
Crapper is clever; a perfectly acceptable reference to a plumber who obtained several patents relating to the much-appreciated advancement from chamber pots.
For those offended by Crapper, you'd probably be even more horrified by a clue where the answer is one of his patents, the floating ballcock.

@Bonnie Ann 

Both can mean "catch sight of." I made out/espied a figure in the distance....

Just some slightly stretchy cluing (on top of a lot of other stretchy clues). I agree this puzzle was a full mental workout.
